text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia diaphyllodinea is a shrub belonging to the genus Acacia and the subgenus Phyllodineae. It is native to an area in the Goldfields-Esperance region of Western Australia.The spreading shrub typically grows to a height of 0.3 to 1.0 metre (1 to 3 ft). It blooms from June to September and produces yellow flowers.
